abstract: It was the last question of the last debate of the year and Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar, who differ on many policy issues, were united in their answer.
snippet: It was the last question of the last debate of the year and Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar, who differ on many policy issues, were united in their answer.
lead_paragraph: It was the last question of the Democratic debate on Thursday, and the candidates were thrown a curveball. They could give a “gift” to someone else onstage. Or, in the “spirit of the season,” they could ask for forgiveness.

abstract: Making a case for the nomination, onstage together for one last time in 2019.
snippet: Making a case for the nomination, onstage together for one last time in 2019.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Elizabeth Warren argued that Democrats would defeat President Trump if they “draw the sharpest distinction” with what she called the administration’s corruption — and suggested that Mayor Pete Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raising would undermine their ability to do that. Mr. Buttigieg said his party could scarcely afford to hew to such “purity tests” in a race against Mr. Trump.

abstract: The seven candidates excoriated President Trump, then turned on one another, as tension between Elizabeth Warren and Pete Buttigieg, building for weeks, broke into the open.
snippet: The seven candidates excoriated President Trump, then turned on one another, as tension between Elizabeth Warren and Pete Buttigieg, building for weeks, broke into the open.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., was repeatedly pushed onto the defensive in the sixth Democratic presidential debate on Thursday night, as several of his rivals challenged his political ascent by bluntly questioning his fund-raising practices and credentials for the presidency in a contentious and deeply substantive forum.

snippet: If hour one of Thursday’s debate was a substantive if sedate affair, hour two had significant and even sizzling moments.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — If hour one of Thursday’s debate was a substantive if sedate affair, hour two had significant and even sizzling moments for Mayor Pete Buttigieg, Senator Elizabeth Warren and Senator Amy Klobuchar. Those three candidates are in a fierce battle in Iowa, where the leadoff presidential caucuses are just six and a half weeks away. Here are six takeaways from the December debate:

abstract: It has been over a month since any relevant state-level poll was conducted. So if candidates like Cory Booker or Tulsi Gabbard have made gains in early-voting states, there’s no polling to show it.
